{
  "stem": "26576.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And as long, as I said before, from the moment he came back, and even before he started to think and plan how to leave Sosnowiec and to go more east.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But it wasn't an easy thing, because immediately there came out all different rules, like the Jews-- Jews were not allowed to travel, you know.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "With every day, Jews were shot in the street.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And every day, new-- new things, which were horrible, which we were very scared-- this was the time when I really started to be very scared.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then what I am saying are the most important thing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I don't remember a lot of little, that-- I-- I remember constantly my father saying, we have to move.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We have to go.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We shouldn't be staying with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They'll kill us.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I saw Hitler promised, and he's going to do it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "That was what he was constantly saying.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And finally, he worked out a plan that I should go with that my next door neighbor.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And we should buy tickets, because Jews were not allowed to travel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And my Polish was very good, and I didn't look Jewish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Because it was already started, the difference between Jewish looks and non-Jewish looks-- things that I was never aware of before, you suddenly started to realize that you shouldn't be-- that it's not good to-- to have a long nose, and it's not good to have brown eyes, you know, because that sort is something that-- that-- that-- So-- so we went.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We bought tickets for-- for the night train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And all of us, which is without my father, which is my mother and the three kids and Mrs.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Krupska.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "This was the Polish woman.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
